<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Grind" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Grind,</orth> (Partic. <cit><quote>ground,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 58</bibl></cit>), 1) to reduce to powder by friction: <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 187</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 5, 16</bibl>.<lb />2) to whet: <cit><quote>mine appetite I never more will g. on newer proof,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 110.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 110, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the --ing of the axe,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 24</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 58</bibl>.
<lb />3) to afflict cruelly: <cit><quote>g. their joints with dry convulsions,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.259" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 259</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>